# One host path per line. Must be an absolute path to a folder that
# already exists - typically an external/mounted drive, or a subfolder of
# one. Add ":rw" for write access - only needed for folders where you want
# the player's flip feature to be able to replace the original file;
# everything else should stay read-only.
#
# Where drives show up depends on your OS:
#   macOS:           /Volumes/<drive-name>/...
#   Linux:           /media/<user>/<drive-name>/... or /mnt/<drive-name>/...
#   Windows (WSL2):  /mnt/<drive-letter>/...
#
# Lines are mounted into the container at the same path under /media
# (e.g. /Volumes/renegade -> /media/Volumes/renegade).
#
# After editing this file, just re-run ./start.sh - it regenerates the
# Colima VM mounts and docker-compose volumes from this file automatically.
#
# Copy this file to mounts.txt and edit it for your own drives -
# mounts.txt is gitignored since it's specific to this machine.

/Volumes/your-drive/your-folder:rw
